The version you are downloading (this version) is geared for private servers, and not to run on Blizzard servers, however to fix this is easy, just open the WoW folder and edit the realmlist.wtf

Deleted what is currently in there and replace it with the following to access the blizzard servers

"set realmlist us.logon.worldofwarcraft.com
set patchlist us.version.worldofwarcraft.com"

Hope this helps.

You can patch it by changing the realmlist.wtf file to read 
"set realmlist us.logon.worldofwarcraft.com
set patchlist us.version.worldofwarcraft.com"

This will use the Blizz DL'r to patch up to date, then you can change the realmlist.wtf file to whatever server you'd like to play on ...

listen guys, to play wow you have to download normal version too. Burning Crusade is the expansion. 

To play payed, you have to buy normal wow and expansion which is $ 50, then you have to put the serials and make an account and pay addictional fees, about $ 15 a month.

TO PLAY FREE, only way to play free is using wow private servers, its quite simple.

1. Find the private server of your liking just google wow private servers there will be many sites, there is normal wow servers, and high rate servers with custom stuff, etc.

2. Now you have to make a account on the wow private server simply register an account.

3. Now that you've done that you must go to your wow folder and there will be a file "realmlist.wtf" and open it with text edit

4. Erase everything in the text and leave "set realmlist" to the server adress. For example: wowfusion.net.

5. now save it and play and write the name and password of your wow private server account in step 2. 

6. You should play now..
